SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA VOICES / A FORUM FOR COMMUNITY ISSUES: SECOND OPINION; 
COMMENTARY FROM OTHER MEDIA; TIME FOR IRA TO TAKE ITS SEAT AT PEACE TABLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From a commentary by Finbar Hill in the Irish Tribune, a monthly paper 
published in Canoga Park. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It is now over two months since the joint declaration of a charter for peace 
and reconciliation in Ireland was announced. 
</P>
<P>
 Among the most important aspects was the statement that all parties committed 
to the peace process would be able to take part in the negotiations. This was 
an appeal, in particular, to the IRA to declare peace and for their political 
arm, namely, Sinn Fein, to take their place at the negotiating table. 
</P>
<P>
 We can only hope and pray that they heed the wishes of the vast majority of 
the people of Ireland and help establish a United Ireland. 
</P>
