<HEADLINE>
<P>
"DADDY" BRUCE RANDOLPH; RESTAURATEUR OFFERED FREE MEALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "Daddy" Bruce Randolph, 94, a restaurant owner who doled out free holiday 
meals to thousands of people over 60 years.The owner of Daddy Bruce's Bar-B-Q, 
he organized Thanksgiving dinners for people who had nowhere else to celebrate 
and eat dinner. Randolph's charity earned him national attention. He was 
profiled in several publications, including People magazine. When he reached 
93, Randolph explained his reluctance to retire with the rhyme, "Ashes to 
ashes, dust to dust, Ol' Daddy Bruce, done hush this fuss." But failing health 
forced him to close his Denver restaurant last March. On Thanksgiving, a Denver 
food bank offered to pick up where Daddy Bruce left off by organizing a special 
holiday giveaway. In Denver on Friday. 
</P>
