to listeners of NPR's "All Things Considered" as "Mama," a central figure in 
her daughter's commentaries and stories. A collection of the stories was 
published in a book called "When Mama Makes Up Her Mind and Other Dangers of 
Southern Living." The book became a 1993 bestseller. In Beachton, Ga., on 
