<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; LAROCCA REBOUNDS TO BEAT ORANGE COAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Josh LaRocca, coming off a poor start, pitched a six-hitter to help Golden 
West to a 10-1 victory over host Orange Coast on Sunday in an Orange Empire 
Conference baseball game. 
</P>
<P>
 LaRocca (1-2) didn't allow a hit after the fourth inning.He retired 16 of the 
final 17 he faced, including 14 consecutive batters before a ninth-inning 
error. He had allowed seven earned runs in two innings Tuesday in a loss to 
Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Danny Flanagan had two hits, including a two-run triple, and Dustin Martin had 
two hits and scored two runs for Golden West (9-11, 3-6). Robert Prince hit his 
first home run for the Rustlers to tie it, 1-1, in the third. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the 11th consecutive loss for Orange Coast (3-14, 0-6). 
</P>
<P>
 In other Orange Empire Conference games: 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress 6, Riverside 1 -- Rob Crabtree pitched his second consecutive complete 
game for Cypress (18-5, 5-2). Crabtree, a sophomore right-hander, allowed eight 
hits, had 11 strikeouts and didn't allow a walk. He has 24 strikeouts in his 
last two starts and hasn't walked a batter in his last 18 1/3 innings. 
</P>
<P>
 The Chargers scored four runs in the fifth to take a 6-0 lead. After a dropped 
third strike and two errors loaded the bases, Josh Kliner had a sacrifice fly, 
Jason Hodges followed with a two-run double and Andy Gonzales ended the scoring 
with an RBI double. Riverside is 17-4, 7-2. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 7, Saddleback 4 -- Mark Veronda's sacrifice fly scored Jon Gardikas 
to give visiting Fullerton a 5-4 lead in the seventh. Brent Coon added a 
two-run single in the ninth for the Hornets (11-9, 5-4). Tim Walker had two 
hits and an RBI also for Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 David Biddinger had two two-run homers for Saddleback (10-7-1, 5-4). His 
second homer in the sixth tied it, 4-4. 
</P>
