<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARLY MORNING FIRE DESTROYS GLENDALE HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fire gutted a three-story home early Sunday after an explosion that may have 
ignited the blaze, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 About 30 firefighters battled the 12:30 a.m. blaze in the 2800 block of 
Kennington Drive and brought it under control within one hour, but cleanup 
efforts at the scene continued until about 7 a.m., said Mike Hand, a fire 
dispatcher. 
</P>
<P>
 Fire officials said the home was a total loss, and estimated the structure's 
loss at $500,000. The loss to contents in the home was estimated at $50,000, 
Hand said. 
</P>
<P>
 The cause of the blaze is under investigation, Hand said. 
</P>
