<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; CITY WATER MEETS HEALTH STANDARDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Drinking water in Simi Valley in 1993 met all state and federal health 
standards, city officials have announced. 
</P>
<P>
 A staff report to be considered by the City Council today says water supplied 
by the city-owned Waterworks District No. 8 met government health and purity 
requirements. 
</P>
<P>
 About two-thirds of the city's residents are supplied by the district. 
</P>
<P>
 The other third receive water from Southern California Water Co., which has 
not yet released its water quality information for 1993. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
