<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: PANEL ON SENIORS SEEKS NEW MEMBERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY SAILLANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Ventura County group that gives advice on activities affecting senior 
citizens is accepting applications for new members. 
</P>
<P>
 Members will advise the Ventura County Area Agency on Aging, make 
recommendations on funding, and act as a liaison between the agency and the 
senior citizen community, said spokeswoman Karen Mondragon. 
</P>
<P>
 The advisory council meets at least 10 times a year, she said. Applications 
submitted will be forwarded to the Ventura County Board of Supervisors, which 
will appoint 19 members by July 1, Mondragon said. 
</P>
<P>
 Application blanks are available at the Area Agency on Aging office, 505 Poli 
St., Ventura, or by calling 652-7560, she said. Completed applications must be 
submitted no later than April 20. KAY SAILLANT 
</P>
