<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: VOLUNTEERS NEEDED FOR POLLING PLACES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The June primary is fast approaching and Ventura County's elections division 
is seeking volunteers to work polling places. 
</P>
<P>
 The division is seeking up to 2,000 volunteers to serve as election officers 
at polling places June 7, elections assistant Georgia Dennehey said. 
</P>
<P>
 "People just aren't thinking about elections right now," she said. "So we're 
trying to get the word out that we need volunteers." 
</P>
<P>
 To qualify to volunteer, you must be a U. S. citizen, at least 18 years old 
and registered to vote or eligible to register. 
</P>
<P>
 Election officers must be willing to work the full day and must attend a 
training session. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, contact Dennehey at 654-2733. SARA CATANIA 
