<P>
 A Newbury Park couple were injured late Saturday when the driver of a 
suspected stolen vehicle ran a stop sign, collided with their car at a Newbury 
Park intersection, then fled, sheriff's deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
 Manuel Godinez, 24, and his wife, Alma Morales, 26, were treated at the 
emergency room of Los Robles Regional Medical Center in Thousand Oaks, then 
released, deputies said.Another passenger, Edgar Garcia, 29, of Inglewood, was 
not injured. 
</P>
<P>
 The hit-and-run driver, thought to be driving a vehicle stolen earlier in the 
evening from the Oxnard area, smashed into Godinez's car at Avenue de la Playa 
and Calle Turquesa at 11:30 p.m., deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
