ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; ASSISTANT PRINCIPAL WINS STATE HONOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sharon B. Wronka, assistant principal of Sunny Hills High School, has been 
named California's Assistant Principal of the Year by the Assn. of California 
School Administrators. 
</P>
<P>
 Wronka received the award based on her willingness to take risks to help 
students, ability to anticipate problems and success in improving the school's 
learning environment, according to a statement by ACSA. 
</P>
<P>
 "Wronka is a tireless worker both in the schools and in the community," said 
ACSA Executive Director Allan Petersdorf, praising the award winner as an 
example-setter for her peers. 
</P>
<P>
 As Assistant Principal of the Year, Wronka will attend a leadership forum 
later this month in Illinois along with the award winners from the 49 other 
states, New York City and Washington. 
