<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: DANA POINT; CITY OFFERS GRANTS TO NONPROFIT SERVICES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nonprofit groups that provide services to local residents can apply for grants 
from the city. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications are available for the 1993-94 grant program and must be returned 
by April 1 to City Hall, 33282 Golden Lantern, Suite 203. 
</P>
<P>
 City officials say priority will be given to funding requests under the 
following criteria: 
</P>
<P>
 * Local nonprofit groups with active programs have the highest priority. 
</P>
<P>
 * Projects or services that fill needs within Dana Point that are not 
currently being served. 
</P>
<P>
 * Programs that target local residents. 
</P>
<P>
 * Projects that spend a minimum amount on administration. 
</P>
<P>
 * Willingness of groups to share information about the program with the 
general public and the community. 
</P>
<P>
 City officials stress that the money should be spent providing the service 
rather than paying office expenses, administrative salaries or other operating 
costs. 
</P>
<P>
 The applications should give specific information about how the funding would 
be spent, who the grant would benefit and where people live who would be served 
by the program. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information about the city grant program, call Shelley Velez at (714) 
248-3525. FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
