<HEADLINE>
<P>
9 ARRESTED IN LAGUNA SOBRIETY SWEEPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nine people were arrested on suspicion of drunk driving at a checkpoint set up 
over the weekend on Laguna Canyon Road, police said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach police, working with the California Highway Patrol, conducted the 
checkpoint at the 30000 block of Laguna Canyon Road between 10 p.m. Saturday 
and 2:30 a.m. Sunday, stopping more than 800 of the 1,300 vehicles that passed 
through during that time. 
</P>
<P>
 Police conducted field sobriety tests on 39 drivers whom they suspected may 
have been drinking. Police said nine people flunked the test and were taken 
into custody and later released on misdemeanor charges of driving under the 
influence. Three people were also cited for open-container violations, and two 
were charged with marijuana possession, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach police generally set up the drunk-driving checkpoints about once 
a month at various spots around the city. 
</P>
