<P>
 Profitable Qantas May Be Easier to Sell: Qantas Airways reported a healthy 
return to profitability last week, raising prospects that the government may 
sell its 75% stake in the airline this year.The national carrier reported a net 
profit of $50.8 million for the six months ended Dec. 31, contrasted with a 
loss of $259.5 million in the first half of the 1993 fiscal year. Analysts 
expect the government to raise more than $1.42 billion from the sale of its 
stake, based on a net profit for the airline of $106.5 million in 1993-94 and a 
net profit forecast of $177.5 million in 1994-95. British Airways has a 25% 
stake in the carrier. 
