ease transport bottlenecks, the newspaper said. No reason was given for the 
cutback. In January, China moved to curtail investment in new construction 
projects to curb inflation, but it said infrastructure projects would not be 
affected. The new construction budget is 28% higher than the 1993 budget for 
rail improvements, China Daily quoted the Railways Ministry as saying. 
